post_text:
We know that some families are thinking of opting for a Cyber Charter School due to the COVID-19 pandemic.

In this time of uncertainty, we want you to be sure of your school choice before opting for a Cyber Charter outside of our district. The risks are great, and the investment is greater.

C.H.E.C.K. before you choose!

We are offering families the ability to have their students learn from the safety of their own home, virtually. That way, GJSD families can have the Trojan experience and easily transition back into face-to-face learning with their Johnstown teachers.

The connection with the teacher matters!

If you are on the fence about your decision, know that we are here to support you. Call your student's school to discuss their learning options for this school year. We are here for your student's success!

post_text:
Juneteenth - Freedom Day - June 19, 2020

Today marks the 155th Anniversary of when Major General Gordon Granger of the Union Army landed at Galveston, Texas in 1865 with news that the Civil War had ended and that the enslaved were now free. Keep in mind that this was 2.5 years after President Lincoln‚Äôs Emancipation Proclamation.

Today we reflect upon this momentous occasion in our nation‚Äôs history, and we celebrate the journey toward racial equity in our country and our communities.

FEEDING PROGRAM & BACKPACK Delivery Update:

The FINAL DELIVERY of breakfast and lunch for the 2019-2020 school year will be June 1, 2020 and the final backpack delivery will be June 4, 2020.

GJSD breakfast and lunch distribution will resume on June 15, 2020 and food will be distributed ONLY on Mondays and Thursdays for a 7 day distribution:

-MONDAY DELIVERY will contain breakfast and lunch for Monday, Tuesday and Wednesday and

-THURSDAY will contain breakfast and lunch for Thursday, Friday, Saturday and Sunday.

There will be multiple sites used for food distribution and the sites will be communicated at a later date via GJSD Facebook, GJSD Instagram, GJSD website, WJACTV, Tribune Democrat and posted at all GJSD schools.

ATTENTION 8th grade families who participated in the Subway fundraiser for the D.C. trip:

We are sad that our 8th grade students will not have the opportunity to enjoy this trip. Please let your students know that they should stay involved at JHS and they will have plenty of opportunities to enjoy enriching field trips in the future.

Families may return fundraiser cards/money in two ways:

1.) Mail your cash, checks, and cards to the high school:

Johnstown High School
c/o Christian Wrabley
222 Central Ave.
Johnstown, PA 15902

OR

2.) Drop cash/cards at the high school in a SEALED envelope labeled with your STUDENT'S NAME. Please also write on the envelope to tell us what contents are inside. (Ex. Mia Smith, 6 Subway cards, $60 cash)
You may drop off Monday-Thursday (4/20-4/23) between 9am-2pm.

**Please understand that you will eventually be charged for what was issued to you if it is not returned in full. We appreciate your efforts to return the cards & money; and we regret that we won't be able to attend the DC trip together this year.

The Cosmetology Club at Greater Johnstown High School conducted a Salon Night on Thursday, November 21, 2019. Students enrolled in Cosmetology performed salon services from haircuts, and styling to color and highlights that evening. Students were busy learning first hand the real-world applications of their trade skills and competencies.
The students and clients alike enjoyed the evening and showcasing their talents. The Cosmetology Profession is a science-based profession with unlimited earning potential and opportunities.

post_text: JES students along with Service Dog Vanna are asking you to support National Bullying Prevention Month. You can show support by wearing a superhero shirt or costume tomorrow to school. Together we can make a difference.
